snippet.textDisplay:
Yuck. This reminds me of feudal Europe. It will take some time for China to learn, but it is also because of their terrible monarchs and how badly foreign nations split the country up before the PRC. 

These setbacks make it hard for the Chinese, especially inland and impoverished, to be competitive in terms of modern statecraft.
